description: Start in kind of a shallow corner, heading up and right.  Gains a small ledge, then up on face climbing and through a small roof, ending on a slab.  Anchors are on a ledge at the very top, allowing one to walk off or rap in.

name: I'm in Trouble
description: Pull the very low roof to gain a ledge.  Some consider this part runout, because if you fall off the ledge or the first move without clipping, you will deck.  Continue up on vertical face climbing, joining Droopy Corndog up high.  Anchors are on a nice comfy ledge at the top, so you can walk off or rap in from here.  Good rock.

name: Pressing Shish
description: Pull through the wide roof crack at the bottom, gaining a ledge.  The PG rating is for here because of the poor quality of rock.  After the ledge, follow the enjoyable hand/finger crack up to the anchor.  There is good rock on all but the starting roof.

name: Running From Voodoo
description: Start left of the first bolt, maybe clipping it with a single locker, then angle up right through the roof.  After gaining the ledge, head up left, following bolts.  After pulling the small roof, follow a neat finger crack and face ot the anchors.  Mostly good rock, maybe a section of barely questionable holds.

name: Blown Away
description: After a somewhat scabby start this line cleans up after the 2nd bolt . Techy and delicate, it doesn't let up till the chains. Similar in difficulty to Warrior Poet but more sustained.     [also makes for an interesting direct start to WP by stepping right into it at the final crack/bulge]

name: Brooks
description: Climb the bolted face to the roof crack.  Pull into it and continue up the crack system to the anchors.  Mostly good rock.

name: Cleavage
description: 5.11a-c, depending on the holds used.  Traditionally 11c, though.    Good rock and fun face moves take you up the face and between the large bulges at the top.

name: Digital Trauma
description: Start either left of the bolt or on Disco Inferno, then hand traverse under the line.  Crunch up under the roof and explode over it on slopers (you heard me).  After that is a bit of easy slab.  At the headwall, head left, then back right to the anchors.  Good rock.

name: Disco Inferno
description: Start in a left facing dihedral, pulling the roof and heading up and right.  Follow the slab to the left arching hand crack roof.  Follow this up and left to the anchors.  Good rock.

name: Don't Blink
description: Face climb to a ledge with a tree.  OK rock.

name: Freefall Cafe
description: Face/slab climbing, pulling left over a small bulge near the top.  Pretty good rock.

name: Freefall Direct
description: This is a 2 bolt variation for the start of Freefall Cafe.  Thin face climbing for 10 feet or so.  Good rock, though those crimps seem like they may peel off someday.

name: Gary's Route
description: Face climb on mostly good rock, weaving close to and farther away from the dihedral.  Pull into and around the right side of another small dihedral at the very top.  Good rock.

name: Great Grannies Gravy
description: Climb the face of Brooks and Spiders From Mars.  Then "either squirm through the chimney, or heel hook and stem out left on good holds to the first independent bolt."  From there, continue up the face to a beautiful short vertical face at the top.  Good rock.  The middle section isn't awesome quality, but not too bad.

name: Resurrection
description: Start on a ledge above the belay, clipping a bolt from it.  Then head straight up on slopers, going left after 3 or 4 bolts.  This joins Gary's Route after 4 bolts.  Good rock.

name: Spiders From Mars
description: Climb the face to the base of the roof.  Pull into the chimney, then right around the corner to the face.  Climb up to a ledge hight on the route.  Pull the final moves on a face to clip the anchors.  Good rock.

name: Warrior Poet
description: Follow the dihedral to a traverse left on pockets.  Some face moves then lead you to the right angling roof crack.  Follow it up and right to the anchor, never really pulling the roof, though.  Good rock.

name: Z Crack
description: Face climb past the bolt and make a 'walrus move' on to the ledge.  From there, continue up and left in the thin hand crack dihedral to the anchor.  Good rock.

name: Big Weenie
description: Pulls over and left around a roof at the first bolt.  Then head straight up on face holds to the anchor at a ledge halfway up the cliff.  Good rock.

name: Excalibur
description: A squeeze job to the left of Indian Drug Carpet. Start on chossy jugs as most Weenie Wall routes do with a brown bolt hanger, then enter a series of techie balance moves to an abrupt crux beneath the roof. The rest of the clips are glue-ins.

name: Indian Drug Carpet
description: Face climb to the roof, aiming for the 2 foot long undercling.  Then continue up on steep sustained face climbing along the thin seam on the left.  Good rock.

name: Lorain's
description: Upper extension of "Big Weenie"    Shallow groove to large protection placement.    Top out or rap off tree.

name: Magic Wand
description: Face climbing through the first roof, pulling left through the second roof.  Then up on more vertical face climbing.  Watch the last big pocket, it stays wet for awhile.  Good rock, except before the first bolt, which is a little crumbly.

name: Thor's Hammer
description: Start left of Big Weenie on the ledge.  Make powerful moves up and slightly right into the nice undercling.  Then more hard moves over the bulge.  Delicate, though easier, climbing waits above.    Finishes about 15 feet up and left of Big Weenie, so it would be easy to continue up from that to set up a TR if no one in your party is up to leading it.

name: Abandoned Project
description: Abandoned project. Needs more bolts

name: Another Project
description: Another Project

name: Dandelion
description: Climb just right of the pocketed face using good holds to reach the top

name: Gonna leave you
description: This is easy pocket route with a small Traverse at the top. The grade is pretty steady throughout.

name: Hand in my pocket
description: The pocket route just to the right of Gonna Leave You. Great lead for new climbers.

name: Perfect Dark
description: Pull burly moves through the small overhang, stick clip the first bolt.

name: Project
description: This is a project. Supposed to be around the 13+ range

name: Rifle
description: Climb through the face of hanging bloc, pulling down, not out, and follow the bolt line to the top.

name: Screamin' Eagle
description: Pull hard moves on the highest quality limestone. Sustained climbing leads to an anchor

name: Slabby Seconds
description: Starts on Hand in My Pocket then instead of fallowing the pocket line continue straight up pulling in small crimps. Things let up and get easy for the last 8'.

name: Tangerine
description: Climb straight up through an orange streak. Hard and weird move towards the top. Go straight

name: Wasbenator
description: Climb up through a corner system. Fun moves

name: Wicked Googily
description: Be careful not to fall on the ledge. Pull through some hard moves, following beautiful colored streaks in the rock to reach the anchor.

name: Blue Suede
description: Tricky start on arete hold by bathrooms.  Arete is not on! work through slopers to a crimpy rail, go up to lip to finish.

name: Face It
description: Start chest height on the eyes of the "face", don't forget the sidepull for the finish!

name: Some kind of BS
description: right arete

name: Unnamed 1
description: start on jug, follow the pink holds to the top
